<TITLE> Stocks plummet on profit-taking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 5 (bdnews24.com)Markets plummeted on the opening day of the week due to sell-offs for profit after almost three weeks of market gains. Dhaka Stock Exchange's benchmark index dropped more than 100 points the Chittagong Stock Exchange's key index shed almost 200 points. Market experts cited the downturn as a normal phenomenon. "A steep fall in indices is pretty much expected after the huge rise witnessed in the market over the last one month," Salahuddin Ahmed Khan, a former CEO of DSE, told bdnews24.com. Sunday's trading saw more than 85 percent of scrips listed on the twin bourses losing value. "Investors opted for selling to rein in profits after days of gains," said Bashir Ahmed, investment consultant of brokerage firm Stock & Bond. But a portion of investors also went for buying in the wake of lower prices, he added. Meanwhile, the bourses continued to maintain high turnover with the DSE crossing the Tk 9 billion mark and the CSE passing Tk 1 billion. The DSE's turnover stood at Tk 9.85 billion, down from its all time high of Tk 11.49 billion on Thursday. DSE general index or DGEN plunged 103.66 points or 3.37 percent to close at 2966.04. The DSI or all share price index finished at 2483.28, shedding 85.49 points or 3.32 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 lost 79.15 points or 3.15 percent to end on 2430.47. Of the traded 230 scrips, 204 lost and 26 gained. Beximco came out top in turnover with shares worth Tk 1.27 billion traded. But it plummeted in price to Tk 294, down 7.83 percent. Titas Gas followed with a turnover of Tk 874.287 million, dropping 3.20 percent to end on 650.25. Beximco Pharmaceuticals ended on Tk 184.70, plunging 6.29 percent. Shares worth Tk 663.192 million changed hands. Bex Tex Ltd had Tk 663.192 million in turnover and ended on Tk 64.80, slumping 8.21 percent on profit taking. Market major AB Bank saw Tk 371.465 million worth of shares traded; it shed 5.93 percent to close at Tk 989.75. Among the other scrips on the turnover board Summit Power, Lanka Bangla Finance, Shinepukur Ceramics and Square Pharmaceuticalsfell on profit taking. Grameen Mutual Fund One: Scheme 2 rose Chittagong Stocks Indices of the port city's bourse also fell Sunday due to losses in ICT, textile and real estate shares. The CSCX or selective categories index slumped 197.14 points or 2.86 percent to close at 6695.36. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 10348.74, losing 294.12 points or 2.76 percent. The CSE-30 blue chip shed 277.71 points or 3.25 percent to finish at 8248.39. Losers outnumbered gainers by 132 to 21 and one scrip held steady. Turnover on the port city bourse slipped down to Tk 1.37 billion from the previous day's Tk 1.63 billion. Beximco topped the turnover board, with shares of Tk 148.729 million changing hands. AB Bank, Bex Tex Ltd, Beximco Pharmaceuticals and Grameen Mutual Fund One: Scheme 2 were the other turnover leaders.
